"{\"value\":{\"mdx\":\"# Rate Limits\\n\\n:::note\\nAll rate limits are subject to change. The latest limits can be queried via the `https://<REST_NODE_ENDPOINT>/dydxprotocol/clob/block_rate` endpoint.\\n\\nNote that rate limits are applied per account. That is, subaccounts under the same account share the same rate limit.\\n:::\\n\\nHere is an example response:\\n\\n```\\n{\\n    \\\"block_rate_limit_config\\\": {\\n        \\\"max_short_term_orders_per_n_blocks\\\": [],\\n        \\\"max_stateful_orders_per_n_blocks\\\": [\\n            {\\n                \\\"num_blocks\\\": 1,\\n                \\\"limit\\\": 2\\n            },\\n            {\\n                \\\"num_blocks\\\": 100,\\n                \\\"limit\\\": 20\\n            }\\n        ],\\n        \\\"max_short_term_order_cancellations_per_n_blocks\\\": [],\\n        \\\"max_short_term_orders_and_cancels_per_n_blocks\\\": [\\n            {\\n                \\\"num_blocks\\\": 5,\\n                \\\"limit\\\": 4000\\n            }\\n        ]\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Active Fields\\n\\n`max_stateful_orders_per_n_blocks`: How many stateful order **place** attempts (successful and failed) are allowed for an account per N blocks. Note that the rate limits are applied in an AND fashion such that an order placement must pass all rate limit configurations.\\n\\n`max_short_term_orders_and_cancels_per_n_blocks`: How many short term order **place and cancel** attempts (successful and failed) are allowed for an account per N blocks. Note that the rate limits are applied in an AND fashion such that an order placement must pass all rate limit configurations.\\n\\n## Deprecated Fields\\n\\nThese fields are not used at this time.\\n\\n`max_short_term_order_cancellations_per_n_blocks`\\n`max_short_term_orders_per_n_blocks`\\n\\n## Examples\\n\\nExamples assume the values in the provided example response.\\n\\n* 2 long-term orders can be placed for each of the first 10 blocks and then a new long-term order would be rate limited on the 11th block since the limit of 20 long-term orders over the past 100 blocks would apply.\\n\",\"document\":[{\"href\":\"/concepts/trading/limits/rate-limits#rate-limits\",\"html\":\"</header>\\n<aside data-callout=\\\"note\\\"><p>All rate limits are subject to change. The latest limits can be queried via the <code>https://&lt;REST_NODE_ENDPOINT&gt;/dydxprotocol/clob/block_rate</code> endpoint.</p><p>Note that rate limits are applied per account. That is, subaccounts under the same account share the same rate limit.</p></aside>\\n<p>Here is an example response:</p>\\n<pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">{</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">    &quot;block_rate_limit_config&quot;: {</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">        &quot;max_short_term_orders_per_n_blocks&quot;: [],</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">        &quot;max_stateful_orders_per_n_blocks&quot;: [</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">            {</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">                &quot;num_blocks&quot;: 1,</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">                &quot;limit&quot;: 2</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">            },</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">            {</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">                &quot;num_blocks&quot;: 100,</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">                &quot;limit&quot;: 20</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">            }</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">        ],</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">        &quot;max_short_term_order_cancellations_per_n_blocks&quot;: [],</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">        &quot;max_short_term_orders_and_cancels_per_n_blocks&quot;: [</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">            {</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">                &quot;num_blocks&quot;: 5,</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">                &quot;limit&quot;: 4000</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">            }</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">        ]</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">    }</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">}</span></span></code></pre>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/concepts/trading/limits/rate-limits.mdx#rate-limits\",\"isPage\":true,\"text\":\"\\nAll rate limits are subject to change. The latest limits can be queried via the https://&lt;REST_NODE_ENDPOINT&gt;/dydxprotocol/clob/block_rate endpoint.Note that rate limits are applied per account. That is, subaccounts under the same account share the same rate limit.\\nHere is an example response:\\n{\\n    &quot;block_rate_limit_config&quot;: {\\n        &quot;max_short_term_orders_per_n_blocks&quot;: [],\\n        &quot;max_stateful_orders_per_n_blocks&quot;: [\\n            {\\n                &quot;num_blocks&quot;: 1,\\n                &quot;limit&quot;: 2\\n            },\\n            {\\n                &quot;num_blocks&quot;: 100,\\n                &quot;limit&quot;: 20\\n            }\\n        ],\\n        &quot;max_short_term_order_cancellations_per_n_blocks&quot;: [],\\n        &quot;max_short_term_orders_and_cancels_per_n_blocks&quot;: [\\n            {\\n                &quot;num_blocks&quot;: 5,\\n                &quot;limit&quot;: 4000\\n            }\\n        ]\\n    }\\n}\\n\",\"title\":\"Rate Limits\",\"titles\":[]},{\"href\":\"/concepts/trading/limits/rate-limits#active-fields\",\"html\":\"\\n<p><code>max_stateful_orders_per_n_blocks</code>: How many stateful order <strong>place</strong> attempts (successful and failed) are allowed for an account per N blocks. Note that the rate limits are applied in an AND fashion such that an order placement must pass all rate limit configurations.</p>\\n<p><code>max_short_term_orders_and_cancels_per_n_blocks</code>: How many short term order <strong>place and cancel</strong> attempts (successful and failed) are allowed for an account per N blocks. Note that the rate limits are applied in an AND fashion such that an order placement must pass all rate limit configurations.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/concepts/trading/limits/rate-limits.mdx#active-fields\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nmax_stateful_orders_per_n_blocks: How many stateful order place attempts (successful and failed) are allowed for an account per N blocks. Note that the rate limits are applied in an AND fashion such that an order placement must pass all rate limit configurations.\\nmax_short_term_orders_and_cancels_per_n_blocks: How many short term order place and cancel attempts (successful and failed) are allowed for an account per N blocks. Note that the rate limits are applied in an AND fashion such that an order placement must pass all rate limit configurations.\\n\",\"title\":\"Active Fields\",\"titles\":[\"Rate Limits\"]},{\"href\":\"/concepts/trading/limits/rate-limits#deprecated-fields\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>These fields are not used at this time.</p>\\n<p><code>max_short_term_order_cancellations_per_n_blocks</code>\\n<code>max_short_term_orders_per_n_blocks</code></p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/concepts/trading/limits/rate-limits.mdx#deprecated-fields\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nThese fields are not used at this time.\\nmax_short_term_order_cancellations_per_n_blocks\\nmax_short_term_orders_per_n_blocks\\n\",\"title\":\"Deprecated Fields\",\"titles\":[\"Rate Limits\"]},{\"href\":\"/concepts/trading/limits/rate-limits#examples\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>Examples assume the values in the provided example response.</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li>2 long-term orders can be placed for each of the first 10 blocks and then a new long-term order would be rate limited on the 11th block since the limit of 20 long-term orders over the past 100 blocks would apply.</li>\\n</ul>\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/concepts/trading/limits/rate-limits.mdx#examples\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nExamples assume the values in the provided example response.\\n\\n2 long-term orders can be placed for each of the first 10 blocks and then a new long-term order would be rate limited on the 11th block since the limit of 20 long-term orders over the past 100 blocks would apply.\\n\",\"title\":\"Examples\",\"titles\":[\"Rate Limits\"]}]}}"
